comments.commentBody:
@George:<br/>
I don't know if I agree with you re attendance. The expectations are much higher and attendance is linked inextricably to quality of play. It is jarring to see 40,000 empty seats in the San Siro when, say Catania comes to town, yet Borussia Moenchengladbach, in a city of 160,000 regularly draws crowds well over 50,000.<br/>
While United always has 75,000 in attendance, Arsenal almost always fills the Emirates with 60K, yet a poor quality Aston Villa drew 40K for its home match with United, while nearby Stoke's visit only drew 30K, and a fair portion are traveling fans. And plenty of stadia in the Prem are MLS sized and cozy: Craven Cottage, the Brittania, the Madejski, Loftus Road, Liberty Stadium DW Stadium all hold under 30K, and there are plenty of crowds under 20K. Even Chelsea couldn't sell out opening day at the DW and top 20K attendance.<br/><br/>No European league holds a candle to the Bundesliga in attendance
